## 4. Form Validation Errors

### 4.1 Client-Side Validation (Zod + React Hook Form)

**Pattern:**
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod'
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod'
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form'

const rsvpSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email('Please enter a valid email address'),
  adults: z.number().min(0, 'Cannot be negative').max(10, 'Maximum 10 adults'),
  kids: z.number().min(0, 'Cannot be negative').max(10, 'Maximum 10 kids'),
})

export function RsvpForm() {
  const { control, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm({
    resolver: zodResolver(rsvpSchema),
  })

  return (
    <View>
      <Controller
        control={control}
        name="email"
        render={({ field }) => (
          <View>
            <TextInput
              value={field.value}
              onChangeText={field.onChange}
            />
            {errors.email && (
              <Text className="text-red-600" accessibilityRole="alert">
                {errors.email.message}
              </Text>
            )}
          </View>
        )}
      />
    </View>
  )
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Immediate feedback (no network request)
- Type-safe error messages
- Consistent validation across forms

